---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE_NAME, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from "@/data/constants";

const title = `Terms of Service — ${SITE_NAME}`;
const description =
  "Terms of Service for Handymen Network. Read our platform terms, independent contractor policies, liability disclaimers, and user agreements.";
const updated = "April 9, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-brand-green">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-base text-brand-charcoal/70">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      These Terms of Service ("Terms") constitute a legally binding agreement between you ("you" or
      "User") and Handymen Network LLC ("Handymen Network," "we," "us," or "our"). By accessing or
      using our website at handymennetwork.com, our mobile application, or any related services
      (collectively, the "Platform"), you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, do
      not use the Platform.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Platform description</h2>
    <p>
      Handymen Network is a technology platform that connects customers ("Customers") seeking home
      repair and maintenance services with independent handyman professionals ("Handymen" or
      "Pros"). <strong
        >Handymen Network does not itself provide handyman services, construction services, or any
        home repair work.</strong
      > We are not a contractor, general contractor, or employer. All services are performed by
      independent Handymen who use the Platform to connect with Customers.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Independent contractor relationship</h2>
    <p>
      Handymen registered on the Platform are independent contractors and are <strong
        >not employees, agents, partners, or joint venturers</strong
      > of Handymen Network. We do not control, direct, or supervise how Handymen perform their
      work. The service contract for any repair or maintenance job is solely between the Customer
      and the Handyman. Handymen Network is not a party to that agreement except to facilitate
      payment processing and communication through the Platform.
    </p>

    <h2>3. User accounts and eligibility</h2>
    <p>
      You must be at least 18 years old to create an account. You are responsible for maintaining
      the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activities that occur under your
      account. You agree to provide accurate, current, and complete information during registration
      and to update such information as needed.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Customer terms</h2>
    <h3>4a. Booking and payment</h3>
    <p>
      When you book a service through the Platform, you agree to pay the listed menu price plus any
      applicable taxes or fees shown at checkout. Payment is collected at the time of booking via
      our secure payment processor. The price displayed on the menu is the price for the described
      scope of work — no additional charges will be applied without your prior consent.
    </p>
    <h3>4b. Cancellation</h3>
    <p>
      You may cancel a booking before the assigned Handyman is en route for a full refund. If the
      Handyman is already traveling to your location, a dispatch fee may be retained. Specific
      cancellation terms are displayed at checkout and in your order confirmation.
    </p>
    <h3>4c. Property access and safety</h3>
    <p>
      By booking a service, you authorize the assigned Handyman to access the property at the
      address you provide for the purpose of completing the requested work. An adult (18+) must be
      present or access must be arranged and confirmed in your booking notes.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Handyman terms</h2>
    <h3>5a. Vetting and approval</h3>
    <p>
      Handymen must complete our vetting process before receiving job offers. This includes identity
      verification, background check clearance, proof of current general liability insurance, surety
      bond where required by law, and skill qualification for applicable menu categories. Handymen
      Network reserves the right to approve, deny, or revoke platform access at its sole
      discretion.
    </p>
    <h3>5b. Insurance and bonding requirements</h3>
    <p>
      Handymen must maintain current general liability insurance with coverage adequate for
      residential repair work at all times while active on the Platform. Where required by state or
      local law, a surety bond and/or workers' compensation coverage must also be maintained.
      Insurance documentation is verified during onboarding and periodically re-verified. <strong
        >If coverage lapses, the Handyman is automatically suspended from receiving job offers until
        proof of renewed coverage is provided.</strong
      >
    </p>
    <h3>5c. Service standards</h3>
    <p>
      Handymen agree to perform all work in a professional, workmanlike manner consistent with
      industry standards. Handymen are solely responsible for the quality, safety, and legal
      compliance of their work, including obtaining any permits required by local jurisdiction.
    </p>
    <h3>5d. Platform fees</h3>
    <p>
      Handymen Network retains a service fee from each completed job. Fee details are disclosed in
      the Handyman Agreement provided during onboarding.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      <strong
        >TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, HANDYMEN NETWORK AND ITS OFFICERS,
        DIRECTORS, EMPLOYEES, AND AFFILIATES SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL,
        SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA,
        GOODWILL, OR OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES, ARISING OUT OF OR RELATED TO YOUR USE OF THE
        PLATFORM OR ANY SERVICES OBTAINED THROUGH IT.</strong
      >
    </p>
    <p>
      Handymen Network's aggregate liability to you for all claims arising out of or related to the
      Platform shall not exceed the greater of (a) one hundred U.S. dollars (USD $100) or (b) the
      total amount paid by you through the Platform in the six (6) months preceding the event
      giving rise to the claim.
    </p>
    <p>
      Because Handymen Network does not perform the physical services (Handymen do), liability for
      property damage, personal injury, or workmanship issues arising from a service is the sole
      responsibility of the Handyman who performed the work and is covered under the Handyman's
      required insurance policy.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
    <p>
      THE PLATFORM AND ALL SERVICES OBTAINED THROUGH IT ARE PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE"
      WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, WHETHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO
      IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND
      NON-INFRINGEMENT. HANDYMEN NETWORK DOES NOT WARRANT THE QUALITY, SAFETY, LEGALITY, OR
      TIMELINESS OF SERVICES PROVIDED BY HANDYMEN, NOR THE ACCURACY OF ANY HANDYMAN'S
      QUALIFICATIONS, LICENSING, INSURANCE STATUS, OR PROFILE INFORMATION.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Indemnification</h2>
    <p>
      You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Handymen Network and its affiliates,
      officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against any and all claims, liabilities,
      damages, losses, costs, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or
      related to: (a) your use of the Platform; (b) your violation of these Terms or applicable law;
      (c) any dispute between a Customer and a Handyman; or (d) any property damage, personal
      injury, or other claim arising from services performed by a Handyman.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Release</h2>
    <p>
      Customers and Handymen each agree to release Handymen Network from any and all claims,
      liabilities, and damages arising out of or in any way connected with any dispute between a
      Customer and a Handyman, including any injury, death, property damage, or other loss arising
      from services provided by a Handyman. You expressly waive any claims against Handymen Network
      for acts, errors, omissions, or negligence of any Handyman or Customer.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Dispute resolution</h2>
    <p>
      Any dispute arising out of or relating to these Terms or the Platform shall be resolved
      through binding arbitration in accordance with the rules of the American Arbitration
      Association, conducted in the state where Handymen Network is registered. You agree that any
      dispute resolution proceedings will be conducted on an individual basis and not as a class
      action. You waive the right to participate in a class action lawsuit or class-wide
      arbitration.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      All content on the Platform — including text, graphics, logos, software, and design — is the
      property of Handymen Network or its licensors and is protected by copyright, trademark, and
      other intellectual property laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative
      works without our prior written consent.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Account termination</h2>
    <p>
      We may suspend or terminate your account at any time, with or without cause, and with or
      without notice. You may delete your account at any time through account settings or by
      contacting us. Termination does not relieve you of obligations incurred prior to termination,
      including payment obligations and indemnification duties.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Modifications</h2>
    <p>
      We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. Material changes will be communicated
      via the Platform or by email. Your continued use of the Platform after changes take effect
      constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Ohio,
      without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
    </p>

    <h2>15. Severability</h2>
    <p>
      If any provision of these Terms is found to be unenforceable or invalid, that provision shall
      be limited or eliminated to the minimum extent necessary so that the remaining Terms remain in
      full force and effect.
    </p>

    <h2>16. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these Terms? Email us at
      <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`} class="text-brand-green underline">{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
